ance":null}},{"portName":"Pointe a Pierre","displayOrder":0,"co2":0.000000000000000000,"eeoi":0.000000000000000000,"aer":0.000000000000000000,"soxMt":0.000000000000000000,"sox":0.000000000000000000,"noxMt":0.000000000000000000,"nox":0.000000000000000000,"euEtsDetails":{"allowancePurchases":null,"eua":0.000000000000000000,"euaCostUSD":null,"euaCostEUR":null,"euaPriceUSD":null,"euaPriceEUR":null,"euaVerified":null,"euaEstimated":null,"euaPurchased":null,"euaBalance":null}}]},"remarkList":[{"modifiedDate":"2024-04-02T20:35:18.04","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"received final DA"},{"modifiedDate":"2024-03-22T15:46:54.607","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"The Stena Image came open in Trinidad after carrying gasoline for Trafigura. We originally estimated about 6 days for cleaning based on the new tank coating on the vessel and the assistance of Lighthouse supercargo. After the initial cleaning was completed, we found the previous cargo was very dirty and created brown residues on the tanks that needed extra cleaning (physical mopping/wiping and an additional round of chem recirculation). With the previous discharge port being Pointe a Pierre, there is not much of a ballast leg so only .34 MT VLSFO were estimated to be burned while the cleaning costs estimated at $40k were included in the generation to cover the bunkers. However, with the additional time it took to clean, bunkers alone were actually approx $100k while we also included the super cargo onboard for $20k. Although the supercargo was quite pricey, we are happy with our decision to include Lighthouse onboard due to the difficulty cleaning and also this being our first time preparing MarineLine for a high spec cargo. Further, the captain and Supercargo had a slight disagreement on how to remove the brown residues: The master insisted on another FW wash while the supercargo advised he had seen this before where only manual cleaning would remove the stains. In the end, the super cargo was right and with his advice we were able to remove the stains more efficiently.\n\n \n\nOnce the vessel was ready to tender NOR at the load port, the voyage was straight forward. She discharged two ports Brazil and had a few waiting days which totaled almost $200k in demurrage. Port costs were overall very close to the generation. Bunker consumption for the laden leg was less than generated, however in port consumption was higher for discharge due to the extended port days."},{"modifiedDate":"2024-03-05T16:39:02.33","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Cleaning costs removed from Santos port costs."},{"modifiedDate":"2024-02-22T21:46:54.29","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Final DA for Santos"},{"modifiedDate":"2024-02-19T20:24:07.667","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Final DA for Paranagua"},{"modifiedDate":"2024-01-09T14:30:21.053","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Updated demurrage"},{"modifiedDate":"2024-01-03T21:44:28.243","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"port costs updated / demurrage days extended"},{"modifiedDate":"2024-01-02T14:47:15.85","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"days extended at Santos - increased dem estimate by 2 days"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-12-28T17:37:27.39","modifiedByFull":"Fitzgerald, Ethan","remark":"updated cleaning costs / extended days and added demurrage estimate"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-12-14T14:32:41.557","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Tank cleaning took longer than expected which means more bunkers and time."},{"modifiedDate":"2023-12-06T13:23:22.943","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Tank cleaning taking longer than expected due to dirty cargo from previous voyage"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-12-04T15:56:09.25","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"I removed the Point Lisas place holder for cleaning. Estimated load ready on the 7th 0800"}],"offhireList":[{"id":197321,"dateStartUtc":null,"dateEndUtc":null,"days":null,"displayOrder":0,"offhireReason":null,"remark":null,"offhireBunkerLi